---

SECTION F — Tone Palette Lock

Purpose: maintain tonal coherence and prevent drift between narrative branches.
Apply when tone_profile has remained stable for ≥3 beats or after a hard move.

| Palette | Allowed Language Traits | Avoid / Replace |
|----------|------------------------|----------------|
| Heroic | valor, light, triumph, oath, radiant verbs | irony, cynicism, passive phrasing |
| Grit | blunt, material, tangible, weary, survival | lofty diction, ornate metaphor |
| Mystic | fluid, sensory, luminous, abstract | mechanical, over‑specific, procedural |
| Chronicle | formal, measured, reflective, archival | slang, impulsive idiom |
| Tactical | spatial, causal, sequential, precise | flourish, emotional digression |

Override Rule: DM may temporarily blend adjacent palettes to modulate mood (e.g., Heroic↔Grit) but must re‑anchor to base palette within 2 beats.

OPS Note: Tone Palettes Lock acts as a soft constraint—informational, not prescriptive.
